   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Empower 1,000 Students with Civics/Media Program</narrative>
  </title>
  <description>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Civic Life Project will train ten high school teachers in CT cities (Stamford, Waterbury, New Haven &amp; Hartford) how to mentor students in the story-telling process of creating a documentary. Students research, choose, and analyze a public issue that is relevant to their lives and communities. By producing short films &amp; leading discussions at screenings, students learn critical transferable skills while finding their voice and agency within their communities.</narrative>
  </description>
